cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on object classification using deep learning techniques, specifically combining convolutional neural networks and Fisher Vector encoding. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel neural network structure that is end-to-end trainable, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the limitations of Fisher Vector encoding and proposes a solution, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of backpropagation for training the network suggests the involvement of neural networks, which could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on the PASCAL VOC dataset, which is commonly used in multimedia research, suggesting the involvement of cs.MM (Multimedia).
